'''''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 3''' is the third issue in the [[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith|''Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'']] series of comics. It was published by [[Dark Horse Comics]] on [[December 13]], [[1994]].

==Opening crawl==
{{OpeningCrawl
|name=Descent to the Dark Side
|text=After Jedi Knight Exar Kun, in a test of his lightsaber skills, cruelly defeats his Master Vodo Baas, he abandons his teacher and begins a search for the remnants of the ancient Sith race and their Jedi rulers, the Dark Lords of the Sith.

Elsewhere, in the Empress Teta system, Satal Keto and his cousin Aleema lead a planetary attack on Koros Major, the last Tetan planet to resist the Krath dictatorship.

Jedi and Republic joint forces, led by Ulic Qel-Droma and Nomi Sunrider, arrive over Koros Major to deal with the Tetan situation. Sorceress Aleema attempts to terrify the joint forces with Sith illusions, and Satal Keto launches suicidal Chaos attack ships against the Jedi/Republic fleet.

Nomi Sunrider sees through Aleema's magic – but when one of the chaos fighters plows into the bridge of the Jedi/Republic command ship, Ulic Qel-Droma is seriously hurt.

Meanwhile, on the planet Onderon, Exar Kun finds two followers of Freedon Nadd who guide him to a mausoleum on the Dxun moon. There, the spirit of Freedon Nadd himself appears to Kun and orders him to exhume the Sith scrolls hidden in a Nadd's sarcophagus.

With the scrolls to guide him, Exar Kun crosses the Galaxy to one of the lost worlds of the ancient Sith magicians and their dark Jedi rulers.
}}

==Plot summary==
===Mustering the Jedi===
Due to the recent attacks and declaration of war against the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] by the [[Krath/Legends|Krath]], thousands of Jedi converge on the red planet of [[Deneba/Legends|Deneba]] to debate the situation. The telepathic [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Odan-Urr/Legends|Odan-Urr]] presides over the meeting.
On the surface, the Jedi ponder the dangers of the darkness that is the come and its relevance among the prophecies.

While carrying her daughter [[Vima Sunrider]], [[Nomi Sunrider]] notices that [[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic Qel-Droma's]] wound from the [[Battle of Koros Major|previous battle]] has not fully healed. [[Shoaneb Culu]] predicts a [[Great Sith War/Legends|great conflict]] with the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] but [[Oss Wilum]] and [[Tott Doneeta]] think that the prophecies are vague. Also present are Ulic's brother [[Cay Qel-Droma|Cay]] and fellow [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] [[Dace Diath]] and [[Qrrrl Toq]]. Many of the great Jedi Masters, including [[Arca Jeth]] and [[Thon]] are present, but Master [[Vodo-Siosk Baas|Vodo]] has yet to arrive; tormented over the whereabouts of his wayward apprentice [[Exar Kun/Legends|Exar Kun]].

===World of the Sith===
Meanwhile on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], [[Exar Kun/Legends|Exar Kun]] begins his search for knowledge of the dark side. Led by the [[Force ghost/Legends|spirit]] of [[Freedon Nadd]], he ventures through the [[Valley of the Dark Lords/Legends|Valley of the Dark Lords]], where corpses fueled by dark side energies rise and attack. The [[Korriban zombie]]s, mistaking Kun for a tomb robber, force him to flee into the [[Great Temple (Korriban)|Great Temple]]. As he enters, the entrance is blocked off, and the spirit of Freedon Nadd leads him deeper into darkness to come.

===Ulic's proposal===
Back on Deneba, [[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic Qel-Droma]] addresses the crowd arguing that a full-out conflict with the Krath may not be worth it. Suddenly an old man, Master [[Shayoto]], speaks up arguing that the Krath must be dealt with now, less they risk events similar to the disasters of the past. In agreement, Ulic suggest that one could infiltrate and join the Krath, and then take them down from within. This spawns more argument. Shoateb, Dace, and Arca disagree with Ulic, with the latter warning that the dark path leads to destruction.

===Kun's test===
On Korriban, Nadd continues to lead Kun deeper into a Mausoleum for Vanquished Enemies. While there, Nadd collapses the cave, shattering the crystals carrying the spirits of Jedi past, annihilating them and crushing Kun. Nadd tells Kun that only the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]] can save him.

Exar Kun's conflict resonates through the Force, alerting Vodo of his predicament. Vodo, [[Crado]], and [[Sylvar]] are approaching Deneba, and as they arrive, Vodo attempts to reach Kun via meditation, but he only reaches the spirit of Freedon Nadd, who blocks Vodo from reaching Kun. Alone and without help, Kun opens himself to the Dark side, and is healed. The screams of Exar Kun's rebirth echo across the Galaxy and are heard by not only his master, but also the other Jedi on Deneba. Vodo fears that this is the first echo of a storm that will consume the galaxy.

===Triumph of darkness===
All at once, the dark side gains ascendancy, and Deneba is suddenly attacked by a barrage of thousands of [[Krath war droid/Legends|Krath war droids]], deployed by a hidden [[Tetan Corsair]]. A massive [[Battle of Deneba|battle]] breaks out as the servant droids draw weapons and attack the Jedi as well. In the chaos, Master [[Arca Jeth]] is killed. As Ulic's beloved master passes into the Force in his arms, Exar Kun experiences rebirth.

Kun marvels at the power of the dark side, and Nadd tells him of the feats of [[Naga Sadow/Legends|Naga Sadow]] and what lies on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]]. Suddenly, Nadd takes [[Exar Kun's lightsaber/Legends|Kun's lightsaber]] and several [[Tuk'ata/Legends|Tuk'ata]] attack Kun. Through anger and the power of the dark side, he retrieves his lightsaber and slays the beasts, passing the final test. He then begins his journey to Yavin 4.

Following the Battle of Deneba, Ulic grieves over the death of his master. Against the warnings of his friend Nomi, he decides to go through with his mission of infiltrating the Krath and destroying them from within. Though Nomi warns him not to underestimate the power of the dark side, Ulic vows to conquer the dark side of the Force.

